This paper is primarily focused on database systems and their performance on multicore servers. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Database). The paper also discusses the crash-resilience mechanism, which involves logging and replay, indicating a possible connection to operating systems (cs.OS). Additionally, the paper proposes a parallel log-recovery mechanism, which involves parallelization techniques, suggesting a possible connection to distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions static and dynamic analyses, indicating a possible connection to programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of transaction processing, which suggests a possible connection to data structures (cs.DS).
